## Firebase Configuration (Choose ONE method)

### Method 1: Environment Variables (Recommended for deployment)
# Get these from Firebase Console > Project Settings > Service Accounts > Generate New Private Key
FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id
FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL=firebase-adminsdk-xxxxx@your-project-id.iam.gserviceaccount.com
FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\nYour-Private-Key-Here\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n"

### Method 2: Service Account File Path (Easier for local development)
# Download JSON from Firebase Console > Project Settings > Service Accounts > Generate New Private Key
# FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_PATH=./serviceAccountKey.json

## Server Configuration
PORT=8000

## Python Backend URL (for ML model fallback)
PY_BACKEND_BASE=http://localhost:8100

## Notes:
# - If no Firebase credentials are provided, the server will run in "demo mode" with in-memory storage
# - Firebase credentials are sensitive - never commit them to version control
# - The FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY must have \n characters for line breaks (keep the quotes)
